            .col-xl-5.col-lg-5.col-md-12.col-xs-12.align-self-center
              h2 Are We About to Face a Digital Dark Age?
              p Loss of data poses a serious risk to infrastructure and safety. Whenever new storage technologies emerge, there is a risk that old media will eventually become unreadable.
      .jumbotron.home-card.home-bg-blue
        .container
          .row.d-flex.justify-content-center.tiles
              .col-xl-4.col-lg-4.col-md-6.col-xs-12.align-self-center
                h2.fandy The Solution:
                h2#fandyness Storing Data on DNA
                p With the unique properties of DNA and rapidly advancing technologies, we think that DNA data storage will replace existing solutions.
              .col-xl-8.col-lg-8.col-md-6.col-xs-12.align-self-center
                img(src=require("./assets/img/homepage/DNA_text.svg")["default"])
      .jumbotron.home-card.home-bg-light
        .container
          .row.d-flex.justify-content-center.tiles
            .col-xl-3.col-lg-3.col-md-6.col-xs-12.align-self-center
              a(href="https://2021.igem.org/Team:Aachen/Memes")
                div
                  include ./assets/img/homepage/bucket_animated.svg
                  //- img(src=require('./assets/img/homepage/bucket.svg')['default'])
            .col-xl-1.col-lg-1
            .col-xl-6.col-lg-6.col-md-6.col-xs-12.align-self-center
              h2 Extremely High Storage Capacity
              p 
                | The information density of DNA is 
                span.highlight 20000 times 
                | higher than the capacity of current storage technologies.
                | With that, you could fit the information of the whole internet into an ordinary bucket.
                | This could make many data centers obsolete.
      .jumbotron.home-card.home-bg-blue
        .container
          h1 What Could we Achieve with Better Storage Systems?
          .row.d-flex.justify-content-center.tiles
            .col-xl-4.col-lg-4.col-md-6.col-xs-12.align-self-center
              h2 Bring Artificial Intelligence to the Next Level
              p 
                | Training neural networks requires huge amounts of data.
                | With a larger storage capacity, the development of better systems can be accelerated.
            .col-xl-2.col-lg-2
            .col-xl-6.col-lg-6.col-md-6.col-xs-12.align-self-center
              div
                include ./assets/img/homepage/artificial_intelligence.svg
      .jumbotron.home-card.rocket-card
        .container
          .row.d-flex.justify-content-center#rocket-container
            .col-xl-8.col-lg-8.col-md-6.col-xs-12.align-self-center.rocket-container
              img(src=require("./assets/img/homepage/dna_rocket.svg")["default"])#rocket
            .col-xl-4.col-lg-4.col-md-6.col-xs-12.rocket-text
              h2 Efficient Data Transport for Colonization of Planets
              p If humanity one day becomes an interplanetary species, it will be necessary to bring lots of information to space. Since weight is always a huge concern in space, DNA would be an ideal choice as a storage medium for this.
      .jumbotron.home-card.below-rocket-card
        .container
          h1 We Present Enzymatic DNA Synthesis for a Data Storage System
          .row.d-flex.justify-content-center.tiles
            .col-xl-12.col-lg-12.col-md-12.col-xs-12.align-self-center
              - var videopath = require("./assets/img/homepage/promovideo.mp4")["default"]
              +video(videopath, "", 80)

    include templates/footer.pug
